name: Psyche Out White Frame
description:
So my name is Jessica Lindell. Around three years ago, I was found almost dead and unconscious after being pushed off a cliff and supposedly my family was kidnapped... yet somehow I have zero memory of what happened or who my family even was. When I woke up in the hospital that day, I couldn’t even remember who I even was for that matter.

The only thing I remember is something that happened right before I fell and it keeps coming back to me every night... that scared and fearful look in my daughter's eyes as she held out her hand to try and save me. I tried reaching out to her, but I just kept falling further and further away and when she herself realized it was too late, she screamed out “the password is 1923!” before I remember hitting the ground.

I'm now a special agent of the FBI trying to find answers for what happened that day. Despite losing all of my memory, I was given the power to look directly into someone's own inner psyche and see when their heart is hiding the truth. With it, I'm going to crack this case and find out what happened, I swear it!

As our team continues to investigate, we're all finding out that the case and my own life altogether was somehow much more complicated than we all initially hoped. Who am I exactly, where is my family, what is this password and most importantly: why do I have this power?

—---

The Gallery Gehenna Project is a daily art project where there are multiple frames for each individual artwork, each with different types of rarity applied. White frames will initially be given away for free via giveaways. All artworks will be compatible within the Gallery Gehenna Game with each artwork unlocking a playable story segment.
